text: René is a given name. It is used for both males and females. It is common in French- and Spanish-speaking areas. The name comes from the Latin name Renatus. The name René was originally given only to males. In some countries that are not French-speaking, the name is also given to females (sometimes without the accent). This name was ranked #964 on the US Popular Names in 2021. == People == * Rene Russo, American actress and model * René Angélil, Canadian singer/manager * René Descartes, French philosopher, mathematician, and scientist (1596-1650) ==References== Category:Given names
